        "description": {
            "value": "<p><strong>Prerequisites </strong><a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.feats-srd\" data-id=\"OUNj8nXTHwGcEdlh\" draggable=\"true\"><i class=\"fas fa-suitcase\"></i> Oracle Dedication</a></p>\n<hr>\n<p>You gain your mystery’s initial revelation spell. Casting this spell progresses your <a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.classfeatures\" data-id=\"ibX2EhKkyUtbOHLj\" draggable=\"true\"><i class=\"fas fa-suitcase\"></i> Oracular Curse</a>. Use the minor curse from your mystery, but when you progress it again, instead of your mystery’s moderate curse effect, you become <a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.conditionspf2e\" data-id=\"AJh5ex99aV6VTggg\" draggable=\"true\"><i class=\"fas fa-book-open\"></i> Flat-Footed</a> in addition to the effects of the minor curse.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If you don’t have one, you gain a focus pool of 1 Focus Point. You can <a class=\"entity-link\" data-pack=\"pf2e.actionspf2e\" data-id=\"OSefkMgojBLqmRDh\" draggable=\"true\"><i class=\"fas fa-suitcase\"></i> Refocus</a>by reconciling the conflicting nature of your mystery, which also reduces your curse to minor.</p>",
